  "prompt": "What is the remainder when 676767\u2026 unto 900 digit is divided by 999?",
  "response": "To solve the problem of finding the remainder when the number formed by repeating the digits \"676\" until we reach a 900-digit number is divided by 999, we can break this down step by step.\n\n1. **Understanding the structure of the number**: The number is made by repeating the sequence \"676\", which consists of 3 digits. To fill up to 900 digits, we need to determine how many full repetitions of \"676\" fit into 900 digits.\n\n2. **Calculating the number of repetitions of \"676\"**:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Number of full repetitions} = \\frac{900}{3} = 300\n   \\]\n   Therefore, the number can be represented as:\n   \\[\n   N = 676676676...676 \\quad (\\text{300 times})\n   \\]\n\n3. **Expressing the number mathematically**: The number \\( N \\) can also be expressed as:\n   \\[\n   N = 676 \\times (10^{3 \\times 299} + 10^{3 \\times 298} + ... + 10^0)\n   \\]\n   This can simplify using the geometric series formula, where the sum \\( S \\) of the series \\( a + ar + ar^2 + ... + ar^{n-1} \\) is given by:\n   \\[\n   S = \\frac{a(1 - r^n)}{1 - r}\n   \\]\n\n   Here, \\( n = 300 \\) (number of terms), \\( a = 1 \\), and \\( r = 10^3 \\):\n   \\[\n   S = \\frac{1(1 - (10^3)^{300})}{1 - 10^3} = \\frac{1 - 10^{900}}{1 - 1000} = \\frac{1 - 10^{900}}{-999} = \\frac{10^{900} - 1}{999}\n   \\]\n\n4. **Substituting back into \\( N \\)**:\n   Thus,\n   \\[\n   N = 676 \\times \\frac{10^{900} - 1}{999}\n   \\]\n\n5. **Remainder when dividing \\( N \\) by 999**:\n   We need to find \\( N \\mod 999 \\). Since \\( N \\) has the form \\( 676 \\times \\frac{10^{900} - 1}{999} \\), the expression for \\( N \\) itself when divided by 999 simplifies to take only into account the term multiplied by \\( 676 \\):\n   \\[\n   N \\mod 999 \\equiv 676 \\times (10^{900} - 1) \\mod 999\n   \\]\n\n   However, since \\( 10^{900} \\equiv 1 \\mod 999 \\) (by Fermat's Little Theorem, since \\( 10 \\) and \\( 999 \\) are co-prime), we have:\n   \\[\n   10^{900} - 1 \\equiv 1 - 1 \\equiv 0 \\mod 999\n   \\]\n   Thus,\n   \\[\n   N \\equiv 676 \\times 0 \\equiv 0 \\mod 999\n   \\]\n\nIn conclusion, the remainder when the 900-digit number formed by \"676\" repeated 300 times is divided by 999 is:\n\\[\n\\boxed{0}\n\\]",
